    "finalTextLength": 1069,
    "finalText": "I don’t have a published help article for creating a commitment yet.\n\nWhat I can tell you from the app’s current workflow:\n\n1. Go to the right project first.\n2. Open the commitments/financial contracts area for that project.\n3. Choose whether you’re creating a subcontract or a purchase order.\n4. Enter the vendor, scope/title, contract value, and status details.\n5. Attach supporting backup if needed.\n6. Save, then route it for whatever approval flow your team uses.\n\nWhat’s missing right now is a controlled help doc that confirms:\n- the exact screen path\n- required fields\n- whether commitments can be created from the AI directly in your environment\n- approval behavior after save\n\nSo the honest answer is: I don’t have that workflow documented well enough to give you button-by-button instructions without guessing.\n\nTwo ways forward:\n- If you want, I can help you find the exact commitment area by project and tell you what records already exist there.\n- Or I can flag this as missing help-center coverage so the team adds a proper “Create a Commitment” article."
  },
